1)
if you are using expo
npm install -g expo-cli

2)
or you can use
npx react-native init projectname

3)
so it generate few files
inside android we have to create local.properties
in this file give this location and save this will different for another system this you will get in anroid studio
sdk.dir = C:\\Users\\ROS5-PC\\AppData\\Local\\Android\\Sdk

4)
\android\app\src\main inside this we have to create a newfile name as assets

5)
open this location myproject then run cmd 
then run in cmd = npm i or npm install 

6)
then open \android in cmd then run = gradlew clean

7)
then go back to project by run command = cd ..
 
8)
then to open project run = code . 

9)
it will open Visual studio code 
then open terminal then run bundle command = 
react-native bundle --platform android --dev false --entry-file index.js --bundle-output android/app/src/main/assets/index.android.bundle --assets-dest android/app/src/main/res/

10)
then attach your mobile to pc then run =
react-native run-android



